# Safety and Verification

## Hard Boundaries

- Read-only on the target during `infra-scan`. Only `infra-generate` writes into the target, and only after the collision guard passes (explicit overwrite/merge/abort decision when the target already has an accelerator).
- Never read, print, edit, or copy `.env` files, credentials, or anything under a `secrets/`-style path - in this folder or the target.
- Never carry secrets or customer data into a finding, a generated file, or a seeded memory chunk.
- Never force-push, hard-reset, `--no-verify`, or drop database tables/schemas in the target without explicit user consent.

## Evidence Discipline

- Every finding cites a real file in the target (path + line/excerpt where practical).
- Mark confidence: `confirmed`, `inferred`, or `unknown`. Route genuinely ambiguous items to `clarifying-interview`; never present a guess as fact.
- Distinguish `require` from `require-dev` and confirm runtime wiring before marking an integration `confirmed`.

## Verification Gates

- Re-validate the Project Profile against the target's current files before generating; flag any drift.
- Generate only the selected AI-tool edition(s) - never more, never fewer.
- `bootstrap-verifier` must pass before `infra-generate` reports success: valid frontmatter, resolving cross-references, hooks pass `bash -n` and are executable, the seeded memory bank passes `validate.py`, and no template placeholders remain.
